@startuml adaptive-ranking-activity
title AKDB Agent-Authoring - Adaptive Ranking & Memory (D9)
start
:recall resolves candidates (FTS + aliases, optional vector);
:for each candidate read item_memory (use_count, last_used, pinned, salience);
:score = FTS x authority x recency x confidence x salience;
if (pinned?) then (yes)
  :apply pin boost (guardrails stay on top);
else (no)
endif
:order by score; return ranked neighbourhood with provenance + anchors;
:agent follows / uses some neighbours;
:reinforce salience + use_count, set last_used_at (item_memory);
note right: periodic/background: salience decays with time-since-use;\npinned items never decay out
stop
@enduml
